**Addon roots** (resolved at install time from preset + `agent-toolkit.config.json`):

{{ADDON_ROOTS}}

**Discover modules dynamically** — never hard-code module names in committed rules:

- Use `codebase` MCP `discover_modules(root_hint=...)` to list installed modules.
- Use `read_manifest(module=...)` to inspect a single module's metadata.
- Use `module_dependencies(module=...)` to trace inheritance / `depends`.

**Standard addon layout** (Odoo 12): `__manifest__.py`, `__init__.py`, `models/`, `views/`, `data/`, `security/`, `wizard/`, `controllers/`, `static/src/`.

> The toolkit ships this rule generic on purpose. If your project has a
> stable set of "main custom modules" worth surfacing to the agent, add
> them to `.agent-toolkit/decision-log.md` via `/adr-add` rather than
> hard-coding here — that way the list travels with the project, not
> the toolkit.
